This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Timothy D Rennhack appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Brett Lee Copeland in court for Timothy D Rennhack.  Attorney Abby Rockendorf appeared in court on behalf of Patricia Irene Daugherty  for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Plea Hearing. Parties are still in negotiations and request an adjourned plea hearing date. Court grants request and adjourns matter for a quick date to Judge Franke, RESERVE branch.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Timothy D Rennhack not in court, in custody.  Attorney Brett Lee Copeland appeared by video for Timothy D Rennhack.  Attorney Amy Spanczak appeared in court on behalf of Patricia Irene Daugherty for State of Wisconsin. Case in court for Status Conference. Defendant not produced. Defense counsel advises that they are now in a resolution posture. Case adjourned for a Plea Hearing date to Br 16.
Plea hearing scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Attorney Brett Lee Copeland in court, defendant Timothy D Rennhack not in court, in custody.  Amy E Spanczak appeared on behalf of Patricia Daugherty for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Status Conference. Defense counsel informs court that they received an offer outside of the deadline set by the court. Defense further requests an additional Status Conference date to review with client. Case adjourned to Br 16.  Status conference scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

OFF THE RECORD- Attorney Brett Lee Copeland in court, defendant Timothy D Rennhack not in court, in custody.  Jon R Josephsen appeared on behalf of Patricia Daugherty for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Scheduling Conference. All parties appeared via zoom. Defendant not produced. Defense counsel informs court that they have received discovery, but are still awaiting an offer from the state. Court schedules next court date for a Status Conference and sets 07/26/2022 deadline for the state to turn over an offer to defense counsel. Case adjourned to Br 16.  Status conference scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Timothy D Rennhack in court with Attorney Brett Lee Copeland; both appear by video.  Defendant Timothy D Rennhack in custody.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer B. Rutherford. Court took judicial notice of 17CF5050 & 17CF4249. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 16.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Timothy D Rennhack in court with attorney Travis Schwantes.  Defendant Timothy D Rennhack in custody.  Mark O Thomson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Timothy D Rennhack appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Grayson, Branch 16. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
